Logical Operators

    AND  OR  NOT
    &&   ||  !
Logical and or are used to compare 2  or more conditions
    AND
    true && true->TRUE
    true && false-?FALSE
    false && true ->FALSE
    false && false ->FALSE

    boolean cold=tru;
    boolean rain=true;
    if (cold) {
    Sout("I will stay ay home");
    }

    OR
    true || true->true
    true || false->True
    false|| true ->True
    false || false->False

    Logical not reverses condition.

    Switch Statement -


    syntax

    switch ( variable){

    case value1:
        code A;
        break;

    case value2:
        code B;
        break;

    default:
          code C;
          break;




    }
    Value of case and switch variable must be same
    Default- must be in switch block and it is optional and it can be anywhere is switch block,
    prefered to have it at the bottom

   -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
   Loop -they repeat block of code a number of times(needed to repeat repetitive code)

   4 loops in Java:
   Use when we don't know how many times you will repeat the code
   while
   do while

  Use when you know in advance how many times you will repeat block of code
   for
   for each/advanced for loop/ enhanced for loop